### Step 7: Service-to-User Impersonation (Service acts on behalf of user)
# Service account impersonates a user - scopes based on target user
POST {{Poc.KeyCloak_TokenEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange&client_id=poc-api&client_secret=your-client-secret-here&subject_token={{serviceToken}}&subject_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token&requested_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token&requested_subject=test&audience=poc-api

###

#####################################################################################################################################################
# AUDIENCE SECURITY PATTERN VALIDATION
# These tests validate that the audience-based security pattern is working correctly
#####################################################################################################################################################

### VALIDATION 1: BFF Token Audience Check
# Get a token and verify it has ONLY "bff" audience
# @name bffTokenCheck
POST {{Poc.KeyCloak_TokenEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=bff&client_secret=your-client-secret-here&username=test&password=test123

### 
# Response should contain access_token
# Decode at https://jwt.io - should show: "aud": ["bff"] (NOT ["bff", "api"])
# If you see "api" in the audience, remove the api-audience-mapper from the bff client

### VALIDATION 2: Direct API Call with BFF Token (Should Fail)
# @name directApiCallFail
@bffTestToken = paste_bff_token_here
GET http://localhost:5001/weatherforecast
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bffTestToken}}

###
# EXPECTED: 401 Unauthorized - Token validation should fail due to audience mismatch
# If this succeeds, your API is NOT validating audience correctly

### VALIDATION 3: Token Exchange BFF -> API (Should Succeed)
# @name tokenExchangeSuccess
POST {{Poc.KeyCloak_TokenEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange&client_id=bff&client_secret=your-client-secret-here&subject_token={{bffTestToken}}&subject_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token&requested_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token&audience=api

###
# EXPECTED: Success, returns token with "aud": ["api"]
# This proves the exchange authorization policy is configured correctly

### VALIDATION 4: API Call with Exchanged Token (Should Succeed)
# @name apiCallSuccess
@exchangedApiToken = paste_exchanged_api_token_here
GET http://localhost:5001/weatherforecast
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{exchangedApiToken}}

###
# EXPECTED: 200 OK - The exchanged token has correct "api" audience
# If this fails, check API's JWT validation configuration

#####################################################################################################################################################
# TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE
#####################################################################################################################################################

# PROBLEM: Token exchange fails with "Audience not valid"
# SOLUTION: Configure token exchange permissions in Keycloak:
#   1. Clients -> api -> Permissions -> token-exchange -> Enable
#   2. Create client policy allowing "bff" client
#   3. Add permission linking the policy

# PROBLEM: BFF token works directly against API
# SOLUTION: BFF client has api-audience-mapper
#   1. Clients -> bff -> Client scopes -> Dedicated scope
#   2. Remove "api-audience-mapper" if present
#   3. Keep only "audience-mapper" that adds "bff" audience

# PROBLEM: API doesn't reject BFF tokens
# SOLUTION: API not validating audience
#   1. Check API authentication configuration
#   2. Ensure ValidateAudience = true
#   3. Ensure ValidAudience = "api"

# PROBLEM: Exchanged token missing "sub" claim
# SOLUTION: Original token missing user context
#   1. Ensure password grant is used (not client_credentials)
#   2. Check client default scopes include "profile" and "email"
#   3. Verify Keycloak user exists and is enabled